{
  "doc_id": "45162",
  "text": "Motivations for the specific form of these two scores have come from several domains. These include the random surfer model for PageRank [CITATION_1] consisting of a mixture of random-walk steps and random jumps, as well as results connecting both PageRank and heat kernel quantities to bounds on sparse cuts [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and regularized solutions to the min-cut problem [CITATION_4] . Even here, however, there has not been an argument that any of these measures are optimally combining the random walk landing probabilities under a specific objective, nor has there been a direct connection between any of these measures and the problem that seed expansion seeks to solve.",
